<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12215b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12215b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12215b"> 215(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Magennis red hand / race, cuts off hand &amp; / flings to w. post</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">l&apos;insigne de la main rouge &mdash; Dans une course, qui avait pour prix l&apos;attribution d&apos;un territoire disput&eacute; par deux tribus rivales, Magennis, pr&egrave;s d&apos;&ecirc;tre battu, s&apos;&eacute;tait coupe une main et de l&apos;autre l&apos;avait jet&eacute;e au but. <br> <font color="green">[The hero who is the ancestor of a family or a clan, is the person who gave them their crest. Magennis is one of those, the ancestor of Conall Cernach, one of the companions of Cuchulain. He was it who gave them the sign of the red hand which is still used. In a race, which had as its prize the territory disputed by two rival tribes, Magennis, realizing that he was losing the race, cut off his hand and flung it with the other to the winning post.]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) LXXIV</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
